HEADWORD: Xanthamide
<hw>Xanth*am"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Xanth</ets>ic + <ets>amide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An amido derivative of xanthic acid obtained as a white crystalline
substance, <chform>C2H5O.CS.NH2</chform>; -- called also
<altname>xanthogen amide</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

